iIn the past, when I didn't use my computer, I'd simply close the lid.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iThe screen would turn off while Thunder continued downloading files		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iand QQ stayed online. Perfect! :-)		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iHowever, when you close the lid on a Macbook, it enters true standby		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
imode—the internet disconnects, and you can forget about QQ or Thunder.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iQQ can still be kept online via mobile, but Thunder...		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iEven using your phone consumes battery. The phone needs charging, but		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iafter some time in standby, the Macbook automatically hibernates. When		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
ihibernating, the USB ports lose power, so your phone stops charging.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iI've never woken up to a fully charged phone. This bug must be fixed.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iSo I searched online and found a software called Sleepless. As the		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iname suggests, it prevents your computer from going into standby or		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
ihibernation.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
